PY  - 1968
DA  - 1968/06/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/255253
DO  - 10.5465/255253
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 153
EP  - 162
VL  - 11
IS  - 2
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - Responses of sixty regular Air Force personnel to the Schein-Ott legitimacy questionnaire are compared with earlier responses of labor leaders, university students, and company executives. Rank-order correlations among the groups are + .88 or higher. Items of high legitimate influence involve job performance, the work environment, and off-the-job conduct which affects organizational interests. Items of low legitimacy concern private acts not directly involving the job or organization.
AB  - Responses of sixty regular Air Force personnel to the Schein-Ott legitimacy questionnaire are compared with earlier responses of labor leaders, university students, and company executives. Rank-order correlations among the groups are + .88 or higher. Items of high legitimate influence involve job performance, the work environment, and off-the-job conduct which affects organizational interests. Items of low legitimacy concern private acts not directly involving the job or organization.
